{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_8ymq2mwhbag7_3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: ‎Nirogyam App - App Store\nURL: https://apps.apple.com/no/app/nirogyam/id6760662109\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nDiscover Ayurvedic daily routines, seasonal wisdom, natural remedies, mudras, beauty science & more — powered by on-device AI. No ads. No tracking. 100% private. Nirogyam (निरोग्यम्) — ancient Indian wellness wisdom with a modern interface. DAILY ROUTINE (DINACHARYA) Personalized Ayurvedic daily routine based on your dosha and season. Track practices and build habits with the Habit Garden. SEASONAL WISDOM (RITUCHARYA) What to eat, how to exercise, and how to live in harmony with each of the six Ayurvedic seasons. Ritu Sandhi alerts for smooth season transitions. NATURAL HEALING (CHIKITSA) • Gharelu Chikitsa — Home remedies from Ashtanga Hridaya • Saundarya Vigyan — Natural beauty treatments • Panchagavya Chikitsa — Healing with traditional cow products • Mudra Vigyan — Therapeutic hand gestures • Nabhi Vigyan — Navel point therapy FOOD & NUTRITION (AHARA) Ayurvedic spice grid, seasonal foods, Jal Vigyan (water science), Dugdh Vigyan (milk science) — personalized to your dosha. PRAKRITI (CONSTITUTION) Interactive dosha quiz to discover your Vata-Pitta-Kapha balance with personalized diet and lifestyle tips. AYUSHCHARYA CALENDAR Monthly calendar with Nakshatra plants and Rashi herb recommendations. VAIDYA AI (iOS 26+) On-device AI guide for Ayurvedic advice, kitchen suggestions, and remedy finding — powered by Apple Intelligence. 100% private. CLASSICAL SOURCES Charaka Samhita, Sushruta Samhita, Ashtanga Hridaya. • No ads, no subscriptions, no data collection • All processing on-device • Available in English, Hindi, Tamil, Marathi, Bengali & Sanskrit Educational purposes only. Not a substitute for medical advice.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Ritu — Your Personal Ayurvedic Guru\nURL: https://ritu.digital/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nRitu tracks your Ayurvedic constitution and how it shifts week by week, recommends the breath, meditation, and recipe that bring body and mind back to balance, and teaches you the wisdom behind each one.\n[...]\nFor three thousand years Ayurveda has asked one question: who are you, and what season is moving through you? Ritu carries that question forward. Your prakriti — your constitutional dosha — is the lens. Your vikriti — your current state, taken weekly — is the weather. Together they decide what your body, your breath, and your mind need next. Not a goal. A return.\n[...]\nMorning: an intention chosen for your dosha and the season above you. Midday: a breath that meets the energy in the room. Night: a reflection that closes the day in your own constitution's voice. Three moments. One thread. Every recommendation grounded in the Caraka Saṃhitā and the Aṣṭāṅga Hṛdaya, then made personal.\n[...]\nRitucharya\n[...]\nSix Ayurvedic seasons, each with its own herbs, foods, and practice. Ritu watches the calendar and your hemisphere — when monsoon turns to autumn, your recommendations shift before you have to think about it.\n[...]\nThe breath, the sit, and the rituals that hold the rest of your day together.\n[...]\nA sequence built with you, not for you. Reorder, hide, add a step. Ritu suggests — you decide how each day opens and closes.\n[...]\nSet an intention each morning. Note what you noticed after practice. Reflect at night. Three moments, one thread, every day — the spine of a sustained practice.\n[...]\nFree gives you the daily rhythm — a quiz, a few soundscapes, a daily wisdom thread. Ritu Lifetime opens the weekly Vikriti check-in, the full library of pranayamas and recipes, more guided meditations, and the extended Ayurveda guide. One payment, yours forever.\n[...]\n- Dosha quiz with personalized results\n- Moon phase & seasonal UI\n- Daily Ayurvedic message\n- Daily wisdom quote\n- 1 pranayama technique\n- Basic meditation timer (10 min)\n- 3 soundscapes\n- Morning intention\n[...]\n- Weekly Vikriti check-in — read your current state and get suggestions to balance body and mind\n- More pranayama techniques\n- More recipes\n- More soundscapes\n- Extended Ayurveda guide\n- More guided meditations based on your dosha\n[...]\nYou don't need to. The first thing in the app is a 3-minute quiz that figures it out for you, drawn from classical Ayurvedic markers (Caraka Saṃhitā Vimāna 8). You can retake it anytime as your awareness deepens.\n[...]\nThose are libraries — thousands of sessions you have to pick from. Ritu is a guide. It chooses for you, based on your dosha, your season, and the moon. Less browsing, more practice.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Ayushya - AI-Powered Ayurvedic Wellness Platform\nURL: https://goayu.life/\nPublished: 2026-01-15T18:30:00.000Z\nAuthor: Ayushya\nHighlights:\nAyushya - AI-Powered Ayurvedic Wellness Platform\n[...]\nExperience the precision of modern AI harmonized with 5000 years of Ayurvedic healing. Discover your Prakruti and restore balance naturally.\n[...]\n## Ancient Wisdom, Modern Tech\n[...]\nOur platform decodes 5000-year-old scriptures using advanced natural language processing to deliver hyper-personalized wellness plans.\n[...]\nDeep analysis of your unique Prakruti (birth constitution) and Vikriti (current imbalance).\n[...]\n### AI Remedy Engine\n[...]\nPersonalized herbs, diet, and lifestyle recommendations powered by precision AI algorithms.\n[...]\n### Scripture Integration\n[...]\nInsights derived directly from 8+ authentic ancient texts like Charaka Samhita & Sushruta Samhita.\n[...]\nExpert Ayurvedic wellness guidance available 24/7 from anywhere in the world, in any language.\n[...]\nBridging the gap between traditional accessibility and modern need.\n[...]\n- Dosha & Constitutional Assessment\n- 2 AI Consultations / month\n- General Lifestyle Guidance\n- Ayurvedic Knowledge Base\n[...]\n- 5 AI Consultations\n- Personalized Herb & Diet Plans\n- Scripture-backed Recommendations\n- Credits never expire\n[...]\n- 15 AI Consultations\n- Full Constitutional Profiling\n- Personalized Herb & Diet Plans\n- Access to 8+ Classical Texts\n- Progress Tracking\n- Credits never expire\n[...]\n- Unlimited AI Consultations\n- Family Profiles (up to 5)\n- Priority Consultation Queue\n- Seasonal Wellness Programs\n- Advanced Constitutional Analytics\n- Early Access to New Features\n- Cancel anytime\n[...]\nAyushya is an AI-powered Ayurvedic wellness platform that analyzes your unique constitution (Prakruti) and current imbalances (Vikriti) to provide personalized health recommendations. Our AI engine processes ancient Ayurvedic texts to deliver customized diet, lifestyle, and herbal remedy suggestions tailored specifically to you.\n[...]\nOur AI analyzes multiple factors including physical characteristics, mental tendencies, and lifestyle patterns to determine your dosha balance. The analysis is based on classical Ayurvedic assessment methods from texts like Charaka Samhita. While highly accurate, we recommend periodic reassessment as your constitution can shift with seasons and life changes.\n[...]\nAyushya draws knowledge from over 8 authentic Ayurvedic scriptures including Charaka Samhita, Sushruta Samhita, Ashtanga Hridaya, and other classical texts. Our AI has been trained on these 5000-year-old wisdom sources to provide recommendations rooted in authentic Ayurvedic tradition.\n\n---\n\nTitle: ‎CureNatural - Ayurveda App - App Store\nURL: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/curenatural-ayurveda/id6749324237\nPublished: 2026-02-21T20:32:17.000Z\nAuthor: Flutter18\nHighlights:\n(Free) • Ayurvedic body type / constitution (Prakriti) and current imbalance (Vikruti) Assessment • Learn your Vata, Pitta, and Kapha balance and elemental tendencies • View results instantly after assessment -------- Subscription Required Features -------- Personalized Daily Plan (Subscription Required) • Personalized daily routine based on your assessment • Guidance includes: o Healthy habits from morning to night o Herbal support with simple DIY tips for digestion, energy, sleep, and stress o Personalized food lists, intake rules, and circadian alignment o Physical and spiritual practices such as yoga, breathwork, and meditation • Downloadable food guide (PDF) • Includes Yoga diet and Sattvic diet options AI Chef Generated Recipes and Food Preferences (Included) • AI Chef generates recipes for each mealtime • Recipes tailored to body type, imbalance, and preferences (vegan, gluten-free, dairy-free, paleo, and more) • Use recipes as ready-to-eat ideas or learning examples • Save favorite recipes in your food list Ayurvedic Remedies (Included) • Simple non-medical remedies for sleep, digestion, mood, stress, and daily balance • Includes spiritual practices such as chakra and energy-balancing techniques • Add remedies once or schedule them into your daily plan Food Database & Grocery List (Included) • Ayurvedic food database with ~1,000 foods and qualities • Find foods aligned with your body type • Create grocery lists for shopping Dynamic Recalibration (Included) • Adjust wake-up, meal, or bedtime times anytime • Recommendations evolve with reassessments Guided Progress Tracking & Notifications (Included in Subscription) • Track your progress from start of the plan • Stay motivated with progress summaries • Gentle reminders for meals, herbs, yoga, and mindfulness Designed for Holistic Living • Clean, modern, and intuitive interface inspired by Ayurveda • Simplifies daily routines while supporting mindful awareness • Integrates Ayurveda, yoga, and meditation in one experience -------- One-Time Purchase Required -------- Integrated Ayurveda Courses (Purchased Separately) • Learn Ayurveda inside the app with short courses for all levels • Video courses with eBook downloads • Lifetime access to purchased courses, even if subscription ends Downloadable Wellness Plan (One-Time Purchase) • One-time option to download your full personalized plan • Printable format for offline use Access & Subscription Information • Constitution assessment and basic results are free • Personalized plans, progress tracking, and reassessments require a subscription • Courses require purchase; access remains after subscription cancellation • Downloadable plans require a\n\n---\n\nTitle: Ritucharya in the Digital Age: A Smartphone Application for Season-Specific Lifestyle and Dietary Guidance\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t| Journal of Ayurveda and Integrated Medical Sciences\nURL: https://jaims.in/jaims/article/view/5264\nPublished: 2026-04-08T13:02:34.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nRitucharya in the Digital Age: A Smartphone Application for Season-Specific Lifestyle and Dietary Guidance | Journal of Ayurveda and Integrated Medical Sciences\n[...]\n# Ritucharya in\n[...]\n: A Smartphone Application for Season-Specific Lifestyle and Dietary Guidance\n[...]\nAyurveda, digitalisation, lifestyle modifications, Mobile application, Ritucharya, technology\n[...]\nBackground: Human health is closely influenced by seasonal and environmental variations. Classical Ayurvedic texts emphasize Ritucharya—season-specific dietary and lifestyle regimens—to maintain physiological balance and prevent disease. In modern India, lifestyle-related disorders such as obesity, metabolic syndrome, and under nutrition have become prevalent due to sedentary habits and dietary shifts.\n[...]\nObjective: The Charya application was developed to translate classical Ayurvedic principles of Ritucharya into an accessible digital platform, providing evidence-based guidance for preventive health and seasonal wellness.\n[...]\nMethods: Classical Ayurvedic texts, including the Brihattrayi (Charaka Samhita, Sushruta Samhita, Ashtanga Hrudaya) and Laghutrayi (Bhavaprakasha Nighantu, Sharangdhara Samhita, Madhavnidana), along with commentaries and contemporary scholarly literature, were reviewed to extract season-specific dietary, lifestyle, and therapeutic recommendations. Data were organized by season and conceptualized in accordance with the Ayurvedic understanding of Kala (time), Adana (Uttarayana) and Visarga (Dakshinayana) phases, and six classical seasons (Ritus). The app was designed in collaboration with software engineers to ensure user-friendly navigation, simplified content, and accessibility for the general population.\n[...]\nResults: Charya provides month-wise seasonal regimens, dietary and lifestyle recommendations, and Ayurvedic home remedies. The app empowers users to align daily routines with seasonal changes, promoting health maintenance, disease prevention, and overall well-being. It also serves as a reference tool for Ayurvedic practitioners and scholars. Limitations include generalized recommendations without accounting for regional climatic variations and the absence of personalized guidance based on individual constitution (Prakriti).\n[...]\nConclusion: Charya demonstrates the successful translation of classical Ritucharya principles into a modern, digital platform. By integrating traditional wisdom with contemporary technology, the application supports preventive health, enhances public awareness of Ayurvedic seasonal regimens, and bridges the gap between ancient knowledge and modern lifestyle needs. Future updates may incorporate personalized and region-specific guidance to further optimize efficacy.\n\n---\n\nTitle: ‎Ayurveda: Dinacharya App App - App Store\nURL: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/ayurveda-dinacharya-app/id1511795722\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n‎Ayurveda: Dinacharya App App - App Store\n\n# Ayurveda: Dinacharya App\n\nHealth & Fitness\n\nFree · Designed for iPad. Not verified for macOS.\n\nShare\n\niPhone, iPad\n\nStart and end your day right with the \"Ayurveda: Dinacharya App!\" Dinacharya is Ayurveda's morning routine designed to maintain and uphold physical health. Ratricharya is Ayurveda's nightly routine. Both are recommended for health and general well-being in daily life. With comprehensive, listed steps, you'll know what to do to participate in these helpful daily practices. Keep track of your progress by placing checkmarks for each step you complete! With the \"Ayurveda: Dinacharya App,\" you don't ever have to be confused about how to complete Dinacharya or Ratricharya!\n\nmore\n\n## Ratings & Reviews\n\n5.0\n\nout of 5\n\n1 Ratings\n\n## What’s New\n\nAdded visual feedback (grey flash) to table entry cell backgrounds when clicked\n\nmore\n\nVersion 1.0.4 11/28/2025\n\n## App Privacy\n\nThe developer, Divakar Saini, indicated that the app’s privacy practices may include handling of data as described below. For more information, see the developer’s privacy policy.\n\n### Data Not Collected\n\nThe developer does not collect any data from this app.\n\nPrivacy practices may vary, for example, based on the features you use or your age. Learn More\n\n## Accessibility\n\nThe developer indicated that this app doesn’t support certain accessibility features. Learn More about the accessibility features.\n\n## Information\n\nSeller\n\n- Divakar Saini\n\nSize\n\n- 470 KB\n\nCategory\n\n- Health & Fitness\n\nCompatibility Requires iOS 17.0 or later.\n\n- iPhoneRequires iOS 17.0 or later.\n- iPadRequires iPadOS 17.0 or later.\n- MacRequires macOS 14.0 or later and a Mac with Apple M1 chip or later.\n- Apple VisionRequires visionOS 1.0 or later.\n\nLanguages\n\n- English\n\nAge Rating 9+\n\n9+\n\n- ContainsHealth or Wellness Topics\n\nCopyright\n\n- © 2020 Divakar Saini\n\n## More by Divakar Saini"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22c4bbb1-1289-478e-91c5-aaf533a8b7ce","uuid":"6a80e7ef-6614-4df0-bb3b-0d724e4dda1b","timestamp":"2026-06-10T22:36:36.486Z","tool_use_result":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: ‎Nirogyam App - App Store\nURL: https://apps.apple.com/no/app/nirogyam/id6760662109\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nDiscover Ayurvedic daily routines, seasonal wisdom, natural remedies, mudras, beauty